Sentencas: The structural and electrochemical properties of novel anode material Ni-0.6(8a(0.3)Ce(0.2)Zn(0.5))(0.4) have been investigated in the presence of hydrogen, natural gas, ethanol, glucose, and sugar-cane at low temperature of 600 degrees C. Through sol-gel method the proposed oxide material is synthesized.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of multi-fuel based low temperature nano-composite anode for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The power density of the cell at various fuels has been observed and measurements indicate that it varies from 57 to 315 mWcm(-2) at 600 degrees C among different fuels at anode side.

Sentencas: The current study reveals that proposed anode Ni-0.6(Ba0.3Ce0.2Zn0.5)(0.4) is promising multi-fuel anode material for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell, and it does not need to reform hydrocarbon fuels in order to fully utilize the advantage of these cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of multi-fuel based low temperature nano-composite anode for solid oxide fuel cell
